<TITLE> CPB reelects president, general secretary </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 10 (bdnews24.com)  The Communist Party of Bangladesh has reelected Manjurul Ahsan Khan and Mujahidul Islam Selim as president and general secretary. The new central committee was formed at the end of the party's three-day 9th Congress. The concluding session on Saturday announced a 42-member new committee, while the previous committee was comprised 41. In a change to its constitution, the party has reserved for women a third of posts in each tier of the party and made presidium members and secretaries full-time political postings. The president and general secretary will be presidium members in line with their ranks. Newly elected presidium members include Shahidullah Chowdhury, Syed Abu Zafar Ahmed, Shah Alam, Sheikh Moniruzzaman and Shahdat Hossain. The congress also announced a national council of 191 members. The CPB has committees in the country's 60 districts. Apart from that the party has branch committees in Bandarban, Khagrachhari, Sherpur and Munshiganj. The total number of CPB members across the country is 7,300. The ninth congress began on Thursday, with 13 representatives from India, Sri Lanka, Pakistan, Nepal, China, North Korea and Vietnam also attending. bdnews24
